{"sections":[{"estimatedTimeInMinutes":10,"xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.3","projectFiles":"OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip","kind":"hero","backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png","title":"Swift Package integration","chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies","image":"ic_unified_ds.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework for Apple platforms.","type":"text"}]}]},{"tasks":[{"title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","stepsSection":[{"code":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Xcode, in your "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"project package dependencies"}]},{"type":"text","text":", add a new "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ouds-ios"}]},{"type":"text","text":" dependency."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"You can then choose the ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency rule","type":"text"}]},{"text":" you want.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and also the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Let’s say you will use some beta version today, e.g. the version1.3.0-beta.2","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"step","caption":[],"runtimePreview":null,"media":"tutorial-discovery-1-ouds-swift-package.png"},{"media":"tutorial-discovery-1-ouds-libraries.png","code":null,"type":"step","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSSwiftUI"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"They can be embeded inside your ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"target"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" librairies.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesContract","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" library provides the main elements like the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"text":". The theme contract is defined inside it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrange","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesSosh"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesWireframe","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrangeCompact"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSComponents"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensRaw"}]},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSTokensComponents","type":"text"}]},{"text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSModules"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSFoundations","type":"text"}]},{"text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"contentSection":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"mediaPosition":"trailing","kind":"contentAndMedia"}]}],"kind":"tasks"},{"assessments":[{"choices":[{"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":true},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS, visionOS, tvOS and watchOS."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"CarPlay specific cases are not scoped yet."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false},{"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports only SwiftUI."}]}],"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides UIKit components","type":"text"}]}]}],"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice","title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which of these choices is correct?"}]}]},{"choices":[{"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the "},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" product wraps all of them.","type":"text"}]}],"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size.","type":"text"}]}]},{"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter."}]}]}],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?","type":"text"}]}],"content":[],"type":"multiple-choice"}],"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding"},{"title":"Instanciate and inject a theme","action":{"overridingTitle":"Get started","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme"},"kind":"callToAction","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything."}],"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"project","hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)","modules":[{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"kind":"task","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"},{"kind":"assessment","reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"},{"projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-